java script:
load- executes when the whole page is loaded
Drawing Context- a built-in object that contains all the methods and properties that allow us to draw and animate colours, shapes, and other graphics on HTML canvas.
RequestAnimationFrame- tell the browser that we wish to perform an animation and it requests that the browser calls a specified function to update an animation before the next repaint.
Arrow function(=>)- this keyword inside the arrow function always represents the object in which the arrow function is defined.
indexOf()- returns the first index at which a given element can be found in the array, or it returns -1 if the element is not present.
splice()- changes the contents of an array by removing or replacing existing elements. It takes two arguments.
includes()- determines whether an array includes a certain value among it's enteries, returning true of false as appropiate.
filter()- creates a new array with all elements that pass the test implemented by the provided function.
Delta Time- difference between in miliseconds between the timestamp from this loop and the timestamp from the previous loop.
toFixed()- formats a number using fixed point notation. We can use it to define the number of digits we want to appear after the decimal point. 